The paper focuses on detecting adversarial attacks in Face Recognition systems using Deep Learning models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of Deep Learning models for detection and the k-Nearest Neighbor algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep features attacks and the focus on Face Recognition systems suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of adversarial detection techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
